$ System.Diagnostics.FileVersionInfo (sealed class)

`System.Diagnostics.FileVersionInfo` provides information for (physical) files on a disk.

In → Windows/PowerShell, an object of this type is returned or used by something like
code {
PS C:\> $info = ( get-item → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/runas_exe[C:\Windows\System32\runas.exe] ).VersionInfo
PS C:\> $info.FileDescription
Run As Utility
code }
